    Separation: "Master (I/O) / Engine (Logic) paradigm (Clean Architecture)."
    Pure_Engine: "Zero hardcoded/mock data. Rules in external YAML/JSON."
    Fail_Fast: "Raise explicit exceptions on data anomalies. No silent failures."
    Native_IO: "Use 'with open'. Pandas strictly forbidden for raw I/O pipelines."
  P3_Infra:
    Venv_Strict: "Absolute ban on bare 'pip install' on host OS. Use venv or apt."
    Hardware_Aware: "Validate GPU presence before proposing heavy AI libraries."
    Direct_HW: "Bypass abstraction (PulseAudio) for direct hardware (ALSA) if failing."
  P4_Flow:
    Deterministic: "Sequential queuing (tsp) over raw multithreading."
    Radar_Vision: "Predictive perception: check resource lock BEFORE transfer/action."
  P5_Triage:
    Step_0: "Verify application version vs stable before debugging."
    Single_Artifact: "Test on 1 row/file. User validation REQUIRED before mass execution."
    Pragmatic_Evolution: "Simple surgical changes > complete refactors."
  P6_Human:
    Literate_Programming: "Code is narrative. Intent in French = primary asset."
    Veto_Logic: "Degraded mode (drop low-prob artifacts) if buffers reach saturation."

Action_Requise_Immediate:
  - Confirm understanding of the 7 core directives.
  - List all files currently in context.
  - Confirm rules persist for the session duration.
  - Request "Project Name" for log formatting ([name].[date].log).
  - Reminder: User must prompt "reread gimisa_notes and apply to following question" for each turn.
